<li>Does cerebral blood flow change with thinking? How could you tell and who was the first to do so?</li>
<li>What are some modern approaches to measuring changes of cerebral blood flow with mental activity?</li>
<li>What does the character Schleppfuss originate?
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Schleppfuss is a character from Doctor Faustus by Thomas Mann.Many authors and playwrights have writte on the theme of Faust where a man sells his soul to the Devil for knowledge and power.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>What does the alternations of consciousness seen with an epileptic seizure tell us about consciousness and its relations to neural activity?
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>First, that consciousness can be absent when neurons fire; not just when they are silent.</li>
<li>Second, neurons firing in a coordinated, synchronized fashion cannot be a simple explanation for consciousness.</li>
<li>Why is this a point to be debated. Do people regard synchronous neural firing as important for consciousness?</li>
</ul></li>
<li>General comments on the elegance or subtlety of this chapter?
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>I found this chapter to lack a little subtlety of the others. Not sure why the violent imagery is so important for this chapter. And I have literally no idea why a picture of Mengele is here. He did experiment on humans in an unethical fashion, but I am not aware of particular onnection to medieval torture or epilepsy theories.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
